  "original_title": "\u2019\u0b93\u0baf\u0bcd\u0bb5\u0bc2\u0ba4\u0bbf\u0baf\u0ba4\u0bcd\u0ba4\u0bbf\u0ba9\u0bcd \u0b89\u0ba3\u0bcd\u0bae\u0bc8\u0baf\u0bbe\u0ba9 \u0bae\u0ba4\u0bbf\u0baa\u0bcd\u0baa\u0bc1\u0bae\u0bcd 50% \u0b95\u0bc1\u0bb1\u0bc8\u0ba8\u0bcd\u0ba4\u0bc1\u0bb3\u0bcd\u0bb3\u0ba4\u0bc1\u2019",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "'The real value of pensions has also fallen by 50%'",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "Prime Minister Ranil Wickremesinghe has said that the value of the money in the Employees' Provident Fund and Employees' Trust Fund has decreased by 50% and the real value of pensions has also decreased by 50% due to the depreciation of the rupee.",
        "He said this while delivering a special speech in Parliament yesterday (5).",
        "Our plan is to control inflation. Inflation will rise to 60% by the end of this year. The main reason for this is the rise in commodity prices in the world and the fall in the value of the rupee. Due to current inflation and depreciation of the rupee, the value of money in Employees Provident Fund and Employee Trust Fund has decreased by 50% and the real value of pension has decreased by 50%.",
        "Think how this situation affects our senior citizens. Poverty is spreading among all of them. The value of the money they receive is reduced by 50%. Their purchasing power has decreased by about 50%. Presenting positive feedback is easy. But these problems are difficult to answer.",
        "What is the solution to this? Stabilizing the rupee as soon as possible, strengthening the rupee rather than depreciating it. For that purpose, he said, he has implemented a plan to limit the printing of money in future."
      ],
